-- AIG CEO says still waiting for markets to improve for ILFC
-- 
-- Thu Nov 1, 2012 5:02pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/11/01/us-aig-assets-idUSBRE8A01L320121101

 

 (Reuters) - Insurer American International Group ( AIG.N ) is still waiting for markets to improve before trying to take its aircraft leasing business ILFC Holdings ( ILFC.N ) public, Chief Executive Bob Benmosche said on Thursday. 
 In a CNBC interview, Benmosche also said AIG had time to make a decision on what to do with its remaining stake in the Asian insurer AIA ( 1299.HK ). (Reporting by  Ben Berkowitz ; Editing by  Leslie Gevirtz )